FT  04 SEP 93 / Letters to the Editor: 'Rationalists' oppose Maastricht
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr PAUL G BYARD
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, Many people throughout Europe (and other parts of the world) have
serious reservations about the Maastricht treaty, believing it to be leading
European Community countries in the wrong direction with potentially
disastrous consequences. We are neither Euro-sceptics nor anti-European;
Euro-rationalists is a more accurate description.
Paul G Byard,
6 Lobster Bay Villas,
Tai Hang Hau,
Clearwater Bay,
Kowloon, Hong Kong
